{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "21", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "18", "M": "54", "S": "32"}}, "news": [{"title": "Manasum Senior Living plans to invest \u20b9150 crore to develop senior living project in Chennai", "para": "Manasum Senior Living is investing \u20b9150 crore in Chennai for The Madras Pavilion, a senior living project. This development will feature 92 villas and 36 apartments. The company also plans a \u20b9550 crore investment to expand its operations across South and West India.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/manasum-senior-living-plans-to-invest-150-crore-to-develop-senior-living-project-in-chennai/130414527?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-48820/130414527.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Vadodara civic body's built homes fall apart in 20 years", "para": "Residents of Vadodara's JNNURM housing schemes are experiencing poor living conditions. Houses built for the economically weaker sections are showing signs of damage. Issues like water seepage and falling plaster have been reported. The Vadodara Municipal Corporation states the core structures are sound. They attribute problems to seepage and neglect by residents.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/vadodaras-jnnurm-housing-crisis-residents-face-deteriorating-conditions/130414214?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-139739/130414214.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Karnataka HC says sub-registrars must update documents within four weeks", "para": "Karnataka High Court has issued new guidelines for civil and commercial courts and sub-registrars.  These rules aim to speed up the updating of property documents when sale deeds are declared void.  Courts must send decrees to sub-registrars within four weeks. Sub-registrars must then update records promptly. This initiative seeks to prevent unnecessary legal battles and save valuable court time.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/karnataka-high-court-mandates-timely-update-of-property-documents-by-sub-registrars/130415865?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-29664/130415865.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}